(141, 1, '2018-10-17 14:39:23', '2018-10-17 12:39:23', 'When the browser lays out the page, it needs to be able to flow around\r\nreplaceable elements such as images. It can begin to render a page even\r\nbefore images are downloaded, provided that it knows the dimensions to wrap\r\nnon-replaceable elements around. If no dimensions are specified in the\r\ncontaining document, or if the dimensions specified don\'t match those of the\r\nactual images, the browser will require a reflow and repaint once the images are\r\ndownloaded. To prevent reflows, specify the width and height of all images,\r\neither in the HTML &lt;img&gt; tag, or in CSS.', 'Details from Google about  image dimensions', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'details-from-google-about-image-dimensions', '', '', '2018-10-17 14:39:23', '2018-10-17 12:39:23', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/rental-center/?p=141', 0, 'post', '', 0),
